delta_rule_sm120_f32_inverse.patch — FP32 WY T-matrix inverse (variant B).

THE primary long-context precision fix. The stock kernel computes the 64x64
(I + tril(beta*K*K^T))^-1 in FP16: the fp32 KK accumulator is truncated to fp16
smem, then CollectiveInverse runs fp16 HMMA at every blockwise level
(8->16->32->64) with fp16 re-truncation between levels. That per-64-token-block
error feeds the fp32-carried KV state and accumulates with CONTEXT DEPTH
(~3128 blocks at 200K) — fine at 2-4K where the kernel was validated, degraded
at 200K (the 7/8 needle miss), and chunk-count-invariant (both KV arms).

NOTE the judge's "1-line inverse_dtype flip" is NOT mechanically possible:
CollectiveInverse hardcodes fp16 fragments + HMMA MmaF16BF16Op + 16-bit
LdMatrix/StMatrix atoms at every level, and StMatrix8x8x16bOp cannot store
fp32. This patch therefore:
  * adds collective_inverse_f32.py — CollectiveInverseF32, an all-fp32 SIMT
    in-smem row-Gauss forward elimination (identical math to level 1 of the
    fp16 collective, generalized to N=64; ~64^3/6 fp32 FMAs + 64 WG barriers
    per block, overlapped with WG1's QK GEMM — noise vs the GEMMs);
  * _kk_store_and_inv fp32 branch: coordinate-indexed UNTRUNCATED fp32 KK
    store, fp32 inverse, then ONE conversion of the final beta*T operand to
    bf16 (an extra KK_SYNC barrier guards the fp32-read / aliased-bf16-store
    overlap that the fp16 path never had);
  * inverse_dtype = Float32 ONLY when o_direct: the +8 KB fp32 KK smem fits
    only because f32-out deleted smem_o (-16 KB). The bf16-out leg
    (gdn_holo_0) keeps the fp16 inverse and stays bit-identical to the
    shipped export — the packed harness regression check remains valid.

EXPECTED after this patch: gdn_export_f32.py's state cross-check between the
bf16 and f32 legs is NONZERO (the fp32 inverse changes — improves — the
recurrence). Expect state cos ~ 1, max_abs small; o cos ~ 1.

Apply AFTER delta_rule_sm120_f32_out.patch (patch -p1 from /home/ms/flashinfer).

